<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="UTF-8">
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
<title>UI/UX Design Roadmap</title>
<style>
  body {
    font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
    margin: 0;
    padding: 0;
    background-color: #000000;
    color: #ffffff;
  }
  
  .container {
    max-width: 800px;
    margin: 20px auto;
    padding: 20px;
    background-color: #000000;
    box-shadow: 0 0 10px rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.1);
    border-radius: 5px;
  }

  h1 {
    text-align: center;
    color: #ffb6c1;
  }

  .roadmap {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
  }

  .roadmap li {
    margin-bottom: 20px;
  }

  .roadmap h2 {
    font-size: 1.2rem;
    color: #ffb6c1;
    margin-bottom: 10px;
  }

  .roadmap p {
    color: #ffffff;
  }
</style>
</head>
<body>

<div class="container">
  <h1>UI/UX Design Roadmap</h1>
  <ul class="roadmap">
    <li>
      <h2>Understanding Fundamentals</h2>
      <p>Learn the basics of visual design: color theory, typography, and layout</p>
      <p>Study the principles of user experience (UX) design</p>
      <p>Understand the importance of user-centered design and accessibility</p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <h2>Tools and Software</h2>
      <p>Master design and prototyping tools like Adobe XD, Sketch, Figma, and InVision</p>
      <p>Learn to use graphic design tools such as Adobe Illustrator and Photoshop</p>
      <p>Understand the basics of front-end development technologies like HTML, CSS, and JavaScript for better designer-developer collaboration</p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <h2>User Research and Strategy</h2>
      <p>Conduct user research to understand the needs and behaviors of your target audience</p>
      <p>Learn to create personas, user journeys, and user stories</p>
      <p>Develop a strategic design approach based on research findings</p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <h2>Design Execution</h2>
      <p>Create wireframes and prototypes to visualize design concepts</p>
      <p>Perform usability testing and iterate based on feedback</p>
      <p>Understand interaction design to enhance the feel of the user interface</p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <h2>Professional Development</h2>
      <p>Stay updated with the latest design trends and technologies</p>
      <p>Build a professional portfolio showcasing your work</p>
      <p>Network with other designers and participate in the design community</p>
    </li>
  </ul>
</div>

</body>
</html>
